        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_amajyn" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:id="form_d4591e66" xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>amajyn</orth><form xml:id="form_d4591e68" type="participle"><orth>amad</orth></form></form>
                <form xml:id="form_d4591e71" xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>amajun</orth><form xml:id="form_d4591e73" type="participle"><orth>amad</orth></form></form>
                <sense xml:id="sense_d4591e76"><sense xml:id="sense_d4591e77"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>складывать (стену, дрова и т. п.)</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>lay together (firewood)</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense xml:id="sense_d4591e86"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>сооружать</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>construct</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense xml:id="sense_d4591e95"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>строить</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>build</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense xml:id="sense_d4591e104"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>стругать</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>chip</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d4591e116">
                        <quote>dæ mæsyg amajyn fædæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>ты кончил строить свою башню</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>you finished building your tower</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>30</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d4591e135">
                        <quote>rajdydta lygtæ kænyn æmæ ʒy dywwadæs sarʒiny samadta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>стал рубить (дракона) и навалил (из его кусков) двенадцать сажен</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>(he) began to chop (the dragon) and piled twelve fathoms of its
                                pieces</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>32</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d4591e154">
                        <quote>fonʒyssæʒ mækʼ˳yly acamadta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>он сложил сто копен (сена)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>he folded a hundred haycocks</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>118</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d4591e173">
                        <quote>amajgæ-amajyn dūr raxawdta æmæ ævsymærtæj sæ īwy sær asasta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>когда складывали (стену), свалился камень и разбил голову одному из
                                братьев</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>when they were building (the wall), a stone fell down and broke the
                                head of one of the brothers</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Čerm."/><biblScope>95</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d4591e192">
                        <quote>arǧwan kalæg æmæ ærtæ bonmæ amajæg</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>разрушающий храм и в три дня созидающий</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>thou that destroyest the temple, and buildest it in three days</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Марк"/><biblScope>%i15%i
                            29</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d4591e212">
                        <quote>acy dūryl samajʒynæn mæ arǧwan</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>на сем камне созижду церковь мою</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>and upon this rock I will build my church</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Матфей"/><biblScope>%i16%i
                                18</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d4591e231">
                        <quote>(xæʒar) næ akald, ūmæn æmæ amad wyd dūryl</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>(дом) не упал, потому что основан был на камне</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>(house) fell not: for it was founded upon a rock.</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Матфей"/><biblScope>%i7%i
                            25</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d4591e250">
                        <quote>rast dony tækkæ særmæ īs īw amad — uj Tybawacillajy kūvændon
                            ū</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>как раз над самой рекой есть постройка — это святилище (божества)
                                Тбауацилла</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>just above the river itself there is a building — this is the
                                sanctuary (of the deity) Tbawatsill.</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Čerm."/><biblScope>90</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d4591e269">
                        <quote>agurijæ amad aǧ˳yst</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>дом, построенный из кирпича</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>house built of bricks</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Puškin._Arhau"/><biblScope>8</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d4591e288">
                        <quote>fyngtæ samadtoj syǧdæg moqotæj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>вытесали столы из чистого (дерева) %smoqo%s</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>tables were cut out of a pure %smoqo%s wood</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>172</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d4591e307" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>samajuncæ tumbul fingæbæl ængulʒæxtæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>затевают на круглом столе пляску на носках</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>they start a dance on tiptoe on the round table</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭп."/><biblScope>62%l338%l</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Старое сращение преверба %iа%i- с %imā%i- ‘мерить’, ‘приводить в
                    порядок’ и пр.; ср. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4591e469" xml:id="mentioned_d4591e332" xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>āmādan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4591e474" xml:id="mentioned_d4591e337" xml:lang="fa"><w>āmāy-</w>
                        <gloss><q>приготовлять</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4591e480" xml:id="mentioned_d4591e343" xml:lang="ydg"><lang/>
                        <w>mā</w>
                        <gloss><q>мерить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4591e488" xml:id="mentioned_d4591e351" xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*āmate(''mtyy)</w>
                        <gloss><q>готовый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4591e496" xml:id="mentioned_d4591e359" xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>māy-</w>
                        <gloss><q>строить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4591e505" xml:id="mentioned_d4591e368" xml:lang="ae"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>мерить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4591e511" xml:id="mentioned_d4591e374" xml:lang="ae"><w>āmāy-</w>
                        <gloss><q>испытывать себя</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4591e517" xml:id="mentioned_d4591e380" xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>mā-: mimāti</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4591e522" xml:id="mentioned_d4591e385" xml:lang="sa"><w>ā-mā-</w>
                        <gloss><q>создавать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4591e528" xml:id="mentioned_d4591e391" xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>строить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4591e534" xml:id="mentioned_d4591e397" xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>мерить</q></gloss></mentioned>. Значение ‘строить’ особенно
                    сближает осетинский с ведийским, а также сакским; ср. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4591e541" xml:id="mentioned_d4591e404" xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>hamən-</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (из %iha%i и
                            %imā-%i)</note>
                        <gloss><q>строить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4591e551" xml:id="mentioned_d4591e414" xml:lang="kho"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>сооружать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4591e557" xml:id="mentioned_d4591e420" xml:lang="kho"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>делать</q></gloss><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Konow._SSt."/><biblScope>139</biblScope></bibl>)</note></mentioned>.
                        <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4591e569" xml:id="mentioned_d4591e432" xml:lang="xsc"><lang/>
                        <w>άμαίακος</w></mentioned> справедливо сопоставляется c <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4591e574" xml:id="mentioned_d4591e437" xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>amajæg</w></mentioned>, nomen actoris от %iamajyn%i, и значит,
                    следовательно, ‘строитель’ (<bibl><author>Вс. Миллер</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ЖМНП"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">окт., стр.
                            248</biblScope></bibl>;
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Justi"/><biblScope>14</biblScope></bibl>). Сращение того же корня с превербом
                    %iny%i | %ini%i имеем в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_nymajyn"/> | %inimajun%i
                    ‘считать’ q. v.; по значению ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_dasun"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II
                            49</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>119, 153</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">An old fusion of the preverb %iа%i- with %imā%i- ‘measure’,
                    ‘arrange’ etc.; cf. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4591e332" xml:id="mentioned_d4591e469" xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>āmādan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4591e337" xml:id="mentioned_d4591e474" xml:lang="fa"><w>āmāy-</w>
                        <gloss><q>get ready</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4591e343" xml:id="mentioned_d4591e480" xml:lang="ydg"><lang/>
                        <w>mā</w>
                        <gloss><q>measure</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4591e351" xml:id="mentioned_d4591e488" xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*āmate(''mtyy)</w>
                        <gloss><q>ready</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4591e359" xml:id="mentioned_d4591e496" xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>māy-</w>
                        <gloss><q>built</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4591e368" xml:id="mentioned_d4591e505" xml:lang="ae"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>measure</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4591e374" xml:id="mentioned_d4591e511" xml:lang="ae"><w>āmāy-</w>
                        <gloss><q>test oneself</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4591e380" xml:id="mentioned_d4591e517" xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>mā-: mimāti</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4591e385" xml:id="mentioned_d4591e522" xml:lang="sa"><w>ā-mā-</w>
                        <gloss><q>create</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4591e391" xml:id="mentioned_d4591e528" xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>build</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4591e397" xml:id="mentioned_d4591e534" xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>measure</q></gloss></mentioned>. The meaning ‘build’ brings
                    Ossetic especially closer to Vedic Sanskrit, as well as Khotanese; cf.
                        <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4591e404" xml:id="mentioned_d4591e541" xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>hamən-</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (from %iha%i and
                            %imā-%i)</note>
                        <gloss><q>build</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4591e414" xml:id="mentioned_d4591e551" xml:lang="kho"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>errect</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4591e420" xml:id="mentioned_d4591e557" xml:lang="kho"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>make</q></gloss><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Konow._SSt."/><biblScope>139</biblScope></bibl>)</note></mentioned>.
                        <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4591e432" xml:id="mentioned_d4591e569" xml:lang="xsc"><lang/>
                        <w>άμαίακος</w></mentioned> is fairly compared with<mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4591e437" xml:id="mentioned_d4591e574" xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>amajæg</w></mentioned>, nomen actoris from %iamajyn%i, and means
                    ‘builder’ (<bibl><author>Вс. Миллер</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ЖМНП"/><biblScope xml:lang="en">oct., p. 248</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Justi"/><biblScope>14</biblScope></bibl>). The fusion of
                    the same root with the preverb %iny%i | %ini%i is found in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_nymajyn"/> | %inimajun%i ‘vount’ q. v.; cf. by the meaning
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_dasun"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 49</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>119,
                            153</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
